---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Terms Of Use – DuoTake";
---

<Layout
    title={title}
    favicon="favicon-duotake-32x32.png"
>
    <main>
        <section>
            <h1>{title}</h1>

            <h3>1. Purpose</h3>

            <p>
                DuoTake is a camera application created to help users capture photos and
                videos in multiple output formats, including portrait and landscape,
                during the same recording session.
            </p>

            <h3>2. Use of the Application</h3>

            <p>
                The application is provided for personal and professional content creation
                use, on an "as is" basis.
            </p>

            <p>
                You agree to use DuoTake only in compliance with applicable laws, platform
                rules, and the rights of other people, including image, privacy,
                copyright, and publicity rights.
            </p>

            <p>
                You may not use DuoTake to create, process, or distribute unlawful,
                abusive, or infringing content, nor may you attempt to reverse engineer,
                copy, modify, or redistribute the application without prior authorization
                from the developer, except where permitted by law.
            </p>

            <h3>3. Permissions and Device Features</h3>

            <p>
                Some DuoTake features depend on access granted by you through iOS, such as
                camera, microphone, and photo library permissions. If these permissions
                are denied, certain features may not function correctly.
            </p>

            <h3>4. Purchases and Restoration</h3>

            <p>
                Paid features, if offered, are processed by Apple through the App Store.
                Pricing, billing, refunds, and subscription management are subject to
                Apple’s terms and policies. Restoration of eligible purchases also depends
                on Apple’s systems and the Apple ID used for the original transaction.
            </p>

            <h3>5. Limitation of Liability</h3>

            <p>
                DuoTake is provided without warranties of any kind, whether express or
                implied. The developer is not responsible for:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Loss of recordings, exports, or media files caused by device or system issues;</li>
                <li>Interruptions, overheating, storage limitations, or hardware-specific limitations;</li>
                <li>Creative, commercial, or publishing decisions made based on the app’s output.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>6. Intellectual Property</h3>

            <p>
                All rights related to DuoTake, including its name, design, branding,
                source code, interface, and associated assets, belong exclusively to the
                developer and/or Adriano Souza Costa, unless otherwise stated.
            </p>

            <h3>7. Changes to the Terms</h3>

            <p>
                These Terms of Use may be updated from time to time to reflect legal,
                technical, or product changes. Continued use of DuoTake after an update
                means you accept the revised terms.
            </p>

            <h3>8. Contact</h3>

            <p>
                For questions regarding these Terms of Use, please contact us at:
                <a href="mailto:adrianosouzacostaios@gmail.com">adrianosouzacostaios@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    main {
        padding: 64px 32px;
        max-width: 780px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }
    p {
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    h1 { margin-bottom: 32px; }
    h3, h4 { margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
    ul { padding-left: 20px; list-style: disc; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    li { margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    a { text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
</style>
